                            <comment id="13417000" author="pmoravec" created="Wed, 18 Jul 2012 11:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See client/src/main/java/org/apache/qpid/client/AMQSession_0_10.java file:&lt;br/&gt;
sendQueueBind method (that invokes getQpidSession().exchangeBind method for requesting the binding to be created) is called from handleAddressBasedDestination just for AMQDestination.QUEUE_TYPE case. I.e. only when the node is queue type and not topic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call of the sendQueueBind method should be irrelevant whether the node is queue or topic and whether the node already exists or not. It should be called only when the create: policy evaluates to true.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
